                                            <p>Successful brain surgeons, neurologists, diagnostic and interventional radiologists and expert teams in intensive care area provide a highly specialized treatment on all the turns of cerebrovascular disease. In some cases these conditions are ensured with micro surgery which contains craniotomy, that is, opening the skull and a brain surgeon’s using highly specialized microscope and surgical tools to define the vessels and take the disease under control. Besides this, endovascular brain surgery area which does not necessitate opening of skull has been also possible with usage of developed technologies recently. The brain surgeons who work in coordination with interventional radiologists make a small cut from femoral artery in legs or biracial artery in arms and put microcatheter to this area. Then the brain is reached by the purpose of reaching vascular malformation. Endovascular techniques make the areas of brain reachable which were not reachable in the past. In this way, brain surgeons treat the most dangerous parts of the brain to be reached. Endovascular surgery is a procedure in which minimal invasive techniques are used in the situations like aneurism which means swelling or bubbling of blood vessel. Patient feels less pain in comparison to the conventional open surgery and duration of staying at hospital is shorter. Therefore complication risk is in more minimal levels. Endovascular surgery involves spiral stenting, angioplasty and embolization. <br><br>
                                                Neurovascular disease treatments happen in a short time with radiosurgery. It is a kind of operation which is done by using radiation. Gama knife is a method in which the surgeon treats brain disorders without needing to make cuts. Gama knife is accepted as an effective and highly reliable treatment method.

