                        <h4>Epilepsy Surgeries</h4>
                        <p>Epilepsy is widely seen both in our country and around the world. Patients get medical treatment from neurology clinics before coming to surgical stage. If episode scannot be controlled with medicine, then epilepsy surgery is needed to take the problematic area which causes the episodes. Surgeon recommends patient to get an operation in following conditions: <br><br>
                            • Physical wounds caused by episodes <br>
                            • Suffocation risk if the episode occurs during bath or swimming <br>
                            • Depression and anxiety <br>
                            • Developmental delays in children caused by epilepsy <br>
                            • Risk of death if patient does not have an operation <br>
                            • Weakening of memory and cognitive functions day by day <br><br>

                            Brain surgery experts are mostly using resective surgery method in epilepsy. With this method, a small part of brain is taken out. Resective surgery is most frequently performed on one of the temporal lobes which control memory, feelings and understanding the language. <br><br>
                            In laser interstitial thermal therapy method, surgeon tries to annihilate a small part of brain which causes epilepsy with laser. In laser interstitial thermal therapy method which is a minimal invasive operation method, magnetic resonance imaging (MR) is used for the purpose of directing laser rays. <br><br>
                            In deep brain simulation, a device which is implanted into a deep area of brain to free regular electric signals which trigger episode and disrupt activity is used. Again magnetic resonance imaging is benefited from. And the generator which sends electric simulations is implanted into chest. <br><br>
                            Corpus celotomy means taking out all or part of the corpus callosum area which ties right and left hemispheres of the brain. This method is generally preferred in children who have various diseases as a result of abnormal brain activities spreading from a side to another side of the brain. Besides, hemispherectomy and functional hemispherectomy operations are practiced as well.

                        </p>

                        <h4>Parkinson Disease Operations</h4>
                        <p>Disorders which are caused by Parkinson disease can be prevented by placing millimetric electronic sticks, a small power supply and an extension lead which unites these two in brain. After the operation, the person is monitored and adjustment of electrodes is made. This battery can be controlled with a remote controller by the patient and doctor and its adjustments can be changed. This enabling of control is so important to detect the value which is the most efficient. <br><br>

                            <b> Does the Battery have a Physical Life?</b> <br>
                            Physical life of battery can range from 3 up to 6 years according to the situation of patient and region of brain where it has been applied. When the battery dies, it is enough to change it by an operation under skin in chest without needing an extra operation. <br><br>

                            <b> Do the indications of disease disappear completely after the operation?</b> <br>
                            After the operation of brain battery, trembling, slow movement and the side effects which drug treatment causes and decrease the living quality of patient diminish in a considerable level. Daily activities like tying shoes, buttoning shirts up, drinking water can be met personally.
                        </p>
                        <h4>Herniated Disc Surgeries</h4>
                        <p>Herniated disc is among the diseases which are experienced by one of every four after a certain age. Compression of spinal cord nerve root in waist generally causes pain. Not only herniation of the disc, but also narrowness of spinal cord causes pain. These pains are generally called as radiculopathy or sciatica pains. This is among the most frequent operations which are done in the area of brain surgery. <br><br>
                            In herniated disc surgeries, surgeon takes a small part of the bone on nerve root or the disc under nerve root to eliminate nerve compression or enable the nerve to heal. The most common operation types are microdiscectomy and laminectomy. Also with lumbar fusion method, cease of herniated disc pain in a painful movement segment under the low back is aimed. <br><br>
                            With developing of robotic surgery method in recent years, brain surgery experts have been used microscopic discectomy method to treat herniated disc disease. Happy results are obtained without opening large cuts in patient and diminishing the period of hospitalization by the aim of eliminating lumbar hernia. Patient can be dismissed the day after.

                        </p> <br><br><br>
